caption: Hidden gem in Little Italy! Best smoked meats I’ve had in the city. Friendly owner and staff!
Great customer service and the food is excellent.
Awesome food and fantastic service! I will definitely be a returning customer !
Family of 5 visiting from Texas on vacation.  Excellent service and amazing food.  Will come back when we visit again! Great job County BBQ!
This spot has wonderful service and tasty food. My favourite spot in town. The drinks and food served quick and the rates are economical. Will definitely recommend this restaurant.
Best food ever! Best staff! Loved it and will be back!
Great brisket and awesome takeout packages!

I’ve been waiting for this place to reopen. I’m so glad it did! You won’t be disappointed. I picked up two pulled sandwiches and they were amazing. The sweet potato fries and the corn bread are a must try! Carlos gave us great costumer service.
Nicest staff/ owner and the best bbq in town. Their Mac n cheese is sooooooo incredible
Hands down the best french fries in Chicago and maybe in the entire country.

We arrived at this place for lunch. we heard about this restaurant from many people.  Well, we were not disappointed. we were warmly welcomed by the crew  and we felt very good. The food was just great. We enjoyed every moment and we will visit this place again. Keep it up.
Great flavor and seasoning on the ribs and brisket, and the sides were delicious. Will definitely be back!

Their garlic fries are hands down the best I’ve ever had. The serving is huge, and if you don’t finish them they crisp right back up in the oven! The people are always really kind and attentive. There’s a student discount! I do wish they had more vegetarian options (I would love a veggie or imitation meat burger of some kind!)
Always good when I visit

I highly recommend this place. Amazing BBQ, everything I've had has been wonderful, great place to watch a game, and support small business. The staff is excellent both the front of the house and kitchen staff.  Get the pork puppies, a mix of pork and a hush puppy, it's so good.
Hands down the best spot in Chicago. The smoke meat on point the drinks are good but the corona got us sitting outside. Bqq lovers must go service is amazing and food gets perfect 10 out of 10.
Good quality meats lightly well cooked  nice ambience only the margarita was too diluted amd too much ice for $10

A hidden gem in Chicago’s Little Italy! County Barbeque serves amazing smoked meats at reasonable prices! Their pulled pork sandwich is extremely tasty and the creamy Mac n Cheese will leave you begging for more! They also have a cool small patio in the backyard.

As a former employee, I must keep it 💯 great food, but I must say working with Executive Chef Williams is rough. I mean real rough, but it was all good, great experience. I might go dine there sometime this spring
This place is off the charts.Food is mind blowing good.Dine in the music added to the ambiance.They do have take out
Fine spot for tasty BBQ. I was so full.
Get the pulled pirk chili

I hate to write this review, but I feel like I need to. I’ve been to County 3 times in the past two months or so, and each time was sadly disappointing. I really really want to like this place - the vibe inside is super chill, the service is really friendly and pleasant, and the patio is great, especially in the evening after work.  Sadly, the food is quite low quality for the price and the drinks are quite over priced and watered down. My wife had two drinks and is a super light weight and she said she barely felt anything. The food seems like it’s chronically over cooked, not burned, but definitely drier than it is should be. I love bbq and I’ve had it all over, maybe it’s a different style here, but idk...  Like I said, I really want to like this place, and know it’s Covid, but all three times I was kinda bummed out when I was leaving because I was left disappointed with the quality and price of the food and drinks...
Place is awesome, but small. Recommend the wings withe the spicy BBQ with a old fashion. Make sure you make a reservation.
This place is amazing. Great food, great service.
Their sweet potato fries with lemon aioli dip is amazing!!!
The brisket is just incredible. One of the best I've ever had.
A fav spot for tasty bbq. I was super full. Will surely make a return trip. The bill was reasonable I would say.
A preferred place for BBQ. this place does it for me. this place has a good atmosphere. reminds me of a cafe in chicago i liked to visit.
Very small portions brisket too fatty and no Smoky flavor will not go back again
Great place for quality bbq. The staff was very friendly and attentive.

Wow! I love BBQ and I’ve traveled all over the country eating it - this here is some of the best Brisket I’ve ever had.  Tasty collards too. Quick and friendly service.  Nice patio to sip a drink while you wait.

This place needs to do better. The sides are very small for the price they charge. The tip and link combo is small. Only 2 links and 5 tips for $14. Guessing all their dishes are small, but their prices are high. The Mac and cheese was under cooked and the greens had no flavor. For $48 I could have feed 5 people had I went to Famous Dave's or a local hood BBQ spot. They really need to either make them portions bigger or lower them prices. I almost forgot my beans were sticky and hard as well. Only thing good I had was the brisket.
Great BBQ pulled pork sandwich. Looking to trying the brisket and chicken next time I am there for lunch.

Maybe it was the lack of customers (due to Covid19) that makes it difficult to turn over food quickly.  The ribs I ordered were very dry.  Almost as dry as jerky.  It was a struggle to get the plastic knife to cut through it.  My guess it that they were made early in the day and sat until evening time.  These ribs should have never left the kitchen and served.   I enjoyed the brisket a little better even though it too was dry.  The rib tips were moist but only because they were so fatty and greasy. Kudos to our server who was very helpful and friendly.
Nice atmosphere and very friendly service. The food was crisp and delightful. Will surely recommend this spot to others. Reasonable prices and generous meals. Great work.
Awesome spot to have something when in a hurry. Their customer service is fast, prices are fair, good mood. I highly recommend this spot.
I constantly come buying some food here. I like the rapid service and well cooked dishes. They never disappoint.

Great waiter with nice personality. Pretty decent barbecue(and I'm from the south) and the mac-n-cheese was is amazing. Nice variety of drinks and great weekday deals. Whoever decides the music in the shop has amazing taste.

I ate at the County Ribs on Taylor St. Tuesday, March 4th 2020. I went there for Tipsy Tuesday. It was the worst meal I ever had. The tips were burned and old. The meat taste like it was cooked 3 days in advance. Be ware!

This is a very good place to go with a family. The only thing I don’t like is that the Mac and cheese is not good. The Hamburger was uncooked. But other then that it is really good. I recommend to come here if you have a big family.
I eat in this spot a lot since I work in the area. I have to say their service is always fantastic and they keep the place clean constantly. Pricing is reasonable and they serve big portions.
Worst ribs ever very disappointed the sauce doesn’t even taste like bbq sauce and the meat low quality it’s not worth the money I wasted.. First and last time
Waiter is really nice, ribs are smoked really good, good atmosphere
Great
Awesome greens and that corn pudding is amazing.  Excellent customer service.. I usually order large catering trays for a party. Alway on time and fresh.

I like this place! They offer splendid dishes, their menu is large, The chef in that place is an expert, I enjoy very much eating all their food. The dishes are consistently good, the attitude towards the customers  is agreeable. I  go often to this restaurant and I was never unhappy. Highly recommended.
The meals and service were beyond our expectations. I really liked the vibes of this place. First-rate spot to take the family out for lunch.
Amazing. Great atmosphere, great soundtrack, meat/sides/salad all amazing, kind and courteous staff, amazingly fast service
Great Barbecue food!
Solid. Good smokiness in the ribs.
Good
The rib tips are the best I've ever had. The food is better than Smoke Daddy and the service is much better.
Happy Hour $1 PBR $2 WELL DRINKS $3 RED WINE 15% DISCOUNT FOR UIC EMPLOYEES AND STUDENTS EVERYDAY
Not that bad
Delicious mmmmm We willl be  back

Hidden gem.  Stop in and see these guys and dig into some fantastic bbq.  A1 A++  Dine-In or Carry_Out.  Or as I did,  Dine-In and then ordere Carry-Out for next days lunch.  Fries are fresh and flavorful.   Mac and Cheese is chee-licous.  Note for the boys.....unlock the door at 11:30

From the moment  you step in this place  team give you an excellent feeling. Very courteous team, it is a happy restaurant to hang out with your friends or with your date. enjoyable  cuisine, talented  chef de cuisine, modest  pay and professional  service. Warmly recommended.
Great service, good food. Had pulled pork sandwich. A little pricey.

Had a killer burger here after Ren Faire. Really hit the spot. My buddy had the wings and they were super jank and had been sitting under a heat lamp for a while I'm sure. The server saw this and without asking brought him a plate with like 6 extra wings.  Super thoughtful and turned a potentially negative experience around. Beautiful building too, really dig the vibe.

Great food and great service. Brisket, pulled pork, spicy wings, collard greens all amazing. Cole slaw - awesome. Everything was top notch including service. We will keep coming back. Good music, good atmosphere, and good food - what else do you need?
Staff was great, very welcoming. Had beers and food. Wasn’t THAT great, compared to a few years ago. Their food needs a little more love.
Tried this place already with my friend and I am hooked ever since. I enjoy the great atmosphere and fresh dishes and drinks. Kudos.

1st and last time I will visit after fire. The place was empty at lunch time and that should have been a red flag. $14 for 2 pieces of brisket which tasted like pot roast. It wasn't bbq. Sauce couldn't save it either. Total disappointment. This place used to be the best. Also, the bar is gone, which was a fun place in addition to the meals. Too bad.

Though I miss the bar that was lost in the fire and remodel, County remains my favorite BBQ spot in the city. The brisket is perfect every time, and the sides are all phenomenal. They also have a great patio space in back.  We even had County cater our wedding and the quality and taste of the food absolutely blew away our guests!
Good BBQ.  Romantic, casual ambience for couples. Music 🎶 is on point!
Carlos the manager and D are always cool and welcoming. Best BBQ in Illinois hands down!!! My Mom has cancer and the chemo kills her appetite...BUT - She will eat County Barbeque👍👍👍 Thanks Guys!!!

Ordered on Caviar. While the food was fresh and hot when it arrived, I have to say the taste was disappointing. Generally speaking, I would call the food bland. The coleslaw was incredibly bland (there’s no way it isn’t just cabbage and mayonnaise); the sweet pickles on top were a saving grace but there were too few. The mac had WAY too much breadcrumbs on top. The pulled pork sandwich wasn’t pulled and didn’t have the signature texture I look for in a pulled pork sandwich. I’m still not sure if I didn’t get the brisket sandwich instead. Overall disappointing, ESPECIALLY the sides, which, for $14, are too overpriced for no flavor.
Great ribs! Loved the dry rub and the house sauce.
(Translated by Google) Very good!!  (Original) Muy buena!!
Flavor was mediocre at best ,  better for the atmosphere!
Great BBQ and dog friendly patio!
Great food, great atmosphere and awesome service, Sam was really nice, you have to try County BBQ's brisket...the best!!!

Service was good, atmosphere quaint, drinks mediocre, but the food was unfortunately awful. We were so disappointed. We ordered a brisket entree and a brisket sandwich - both were about 50/60% fat. We also ordered mac and cheese, cole slaw, and hush puppies. All of which were bland and tasteless, not to mention the hush puppies were hard and slightly burned. The only reason I'm giving two stars is because our server was so friendly and the place was clean.
Absolutely amazing meats. Small selection - but what they do, they do well! I highly recommend it to any carnivore who is ready to fall into a food coma with a big smile on their face.
(Translated by Google) It looks very good atmosphere and the meals look delicious ❤❤❤❤❤❤❤❤❤❤❤❤❤  (Original) Se ve muy buen ambiente y las comidas se ven deliciosas ❤❤❤❤❤❤❤❤❤❤❤❤❤

The bbq brisket sandwich is a must! Very tender and well flavored and decent portion size. Thursday they have $15 special you get sandwich, shot of bourbon,  and can of beer. My bestie and hubby poured the bourbon over their brisket and said it gave it a smokey fiery flavor. The pudding corn is basically very sweet cornbread with pieces of corn in it. Highly recommend! I was not a fan of pork puppies, too fried, and it was more like mashed potatoe consistency inside didnt really taste any pork, wouldn't recommend. The mac and cheese was delish. I didnt like the inside venue, too dark and felt like a sauna, I'd definitely would come back for the brisket but would do take out instead of dining in. The guy who waited on us was friendly and offered us the corn pudding because we disliked the pork puppies, great customer service! Way better than honky tonk bbq in pilsen.
Just good food.
The best barbecue in the City of Chicago bar none
Brisket was amazing.  Super soft and juicy. Everything was fresh. Great atmosphere and great specials
(Translated by Google) I like it a lot  (Original) Me gusta mucho
The food was great! Stop by and give em a try 😋👍🏾
It's changed a lot since the initial opening. The food is still good but the menu is very limited. Plus our favorite drink isn't on the menu any longer. It's not our go to place the way it once was 😔

Reopening after a long hiatus, the barbecue remains some of the best in the city and definitely the best in the area.  Don't expect to be wowed by sauces or sides, but meats exquisitely smoked and all star service make this a winner.
You gotta try the Pork Puppies they’re fire!

We were loyal County customers for years before the fire. We have waited and waited for the reopening. Opened yesterday and we returned today. Very very disappointed. Not a fan of the new layout, but that is a personal opinion and can be overlooked if the food was good. The food was not good. The ribs were ok, but nothing I cant get many other places in Chicago. The brisket was just not very edible. It was hard to cut and chew. The exact opposite of how brisket should be. The mac and cheese had exactly no flavor. The only thing we ordered that tasted the same was the corn pudding. We hope they are just going through an adjustment curve. We will try again and update, but feel that it was not at all worth the 2.5 year wait.  UPDATE: gave it another shot yesterday on a beautiful Saturday. Sat on the new patio. Food was AMAZING. Everything was back to how we remembered. We got 6 sides, a brisket sandwich, brisket, and a half rack of ribs. We are in love again and cannot wait to go back!
Great food. Wish they had more choices as far as meat.  Definitely worthy for a trip back.
OMG! Listen, this place is awesome!!! Real BBQ, updated sides and a full bar. You can't go wrong. Sit on the patio for the full experience.

I am in love with their brisket! Such delectable melt in your mouth texture that makes you want to eat more. Their ribs are flavorful with meat that tear off the bone so easily. They also have awesome mac and cheese and corn pudding. The staff always takes care of me whenever I go in. I am so glad that I found this BBQ place. I will be a returning customer for many years to come
If the food doesn't make you want to come back, the people will! Awesome spot, glad we found it!
Glad that this place is back. Food is great, have tried most of the menu items and look forward to heading back to try the rest. Daily specials make it tempting to make this a regular spot :)
Good burger and house sauce
A preferred spot for delicious BBQ. This place will surprise you. The staff was very helpful and observant.
Best restaurant i have been too since i been here. Outstanding service and great food. Thank you!
Great food. Expensive(?) Order of half pound of brisket, half slab, 3 sides, a lemonade, and a Pepsi = $48.
Good brisket and rib tips.  The corn pudding and pork puppies are worth going back for. The ribs are ok and the sausage is decent.   The bbq sauces are awful.   Very surprised by that.
I haven't been back since they reopened.  But before the fire,  you couldn't keep me out of here.  This is the only place in the city where I would order brisket, and their sandwiches were great.
Pulled pork was good and it's pretty cozy.
Meh. Over salted and over seasoned meats that are small portions. Garlic fries and sweet potato fries were tasty.  They make a strong Old Fashioned, but I wouldnt go back.
Good food

Friendly staff, and fun sides - but the meat is pretty low quality, and the sauce is not enjoyable.  When I say low quality, the cuts of brisket (whether on it's own or in a sandwich) are really fatty. I'm okay with a little fat, but this just wasn't good quality. Rib tip seasoning wasn't right either.  For how expensive it is, really not on par with other places who know how to get BBQ right.  Unfortunately after two experiences like this, I won't be returning again.

I ordered rib tips. They came out cold. We also ordered the beef brisket...it also came out cold. The BBQ sauce was acidic. The sides were probably out the best thing I had there. The coleslaw was delish and so were the pickles. Mac and cheese and the sweet potato fries were great. I wish the meat were better and I wish it came out hot and fresh. I was a bit disappointed for the price I was paying. It felt like the McDonald's of BBQ to me. You order at the front and wait for your food. It wasn't even that busy. Maybe I caught them on a bad day. I will probably give them another chance since I liked the calm atmosphere.
Food is excellent; staff is extremely friendly and customer oriented. Tuesdays are 50 cent rib tips, can't beat that deal! Will definitely be coming back to try their chicken deal on Monday!!!

Had the brisket and the rib tips with Mac n cheese, mapled glazed bacon and the hush poppers. Everything was flavorful. I was really surprised with the Mac n cheese to be honest. It was not over cheesed or lacking taste. Even the house spices aren't too overbearing. I will definitely be back.
Glad it's back! Easily the best BBQ in the city.
Glad that it is back from the fire that shut it down two years ago.  Love the brisket sandwiches and the various sides.  Well done.
Just re opened a little while ago. Ordered the brisket and mac n cheese, both were amazing! Price point is right on que for a bbq joint. Highly recommend!
Good food. A little salty but will definitely be trying again.

WOW!!! We moved into the neighborhood about a year and a half ago and have been waiting for this place to re-open.  Our first time was an awesome experience and we will definitely be back.  Ordered 2 entrees and 3 sides and each one was delicious.  The 1/2 chicken was perfectly smoked and the pulled pork sandwich seriously hit the spot.  The corn pudding and pork puppies were probably our favorite.  That along with great cocktails and beer and I don’t know what else you’d want out of a neighborhood BBQ joint.  Would love to see the addition of waiters at some point but that didn’t detract from our experience at all.  Staff was friendly and gave great recommendations.  Come and try it!

County BBQ reopened but the local celebrity chef is no longer on site, the whiskey centric bar scene is no more and there is no table service.  Its a virtually new establishment but still a great place to get some much better than average eats in a casual (but not cheap) setting.  This was my first visit back to the old namesake and, since I had the place all to myself in the middle of a shift change, I didn't get a real feel for the vibe or service but the food was excellent. The brisket was flavorful and (mostly) melt in my mouth tender, the sausage was firm and bursting in homemade goodness and the greens were as good, if not better than, Mr. Williams' (is he still closeby or did he leave recipes?).  I will be back.

Was on a date and was in the mood for some BBQ on a cold day and this place was recommended after doing a google search. The place was empty but we decided to give it a try and glad we did! The rib tips, greens, smoked chicken, and corn pudding were amazing. The mac and cheese lacked flavor and was undercooked. Even a little salt and pepper didn't help it so will skip that next time. The hot links were ok...seemed they could have been smoked/cooked longer. The lemonade was delicious. Sam assisted us and was so friendly and kind and even let us sample the brisket per our request which we will definitely order next time. The cook came out and let us sample the pork hush puppies which was amazing. The brisket was tender,  juicy and flavorful. This place is a must try if you're in the area and looking for some good BBQ. It's worth it. We will be going back!!!

Quality barbeque - all the food - is outstanding.  We got the rib tips, hushpuppies, and beans... deliriously good.  They overcharged us, however. Cute place, nice folks - hung out with the staff and the cook... they gave us some free cured bacon (wow!)!  I drank some cheap whiskey for $5 each on the rocks.  She had the margarita for $11.  It's worth your trip. Even in the frigid cold.

Thank goodness they’re back!!! County BBQ is finally reopened after a bad fire. They have a great selection of meats and sides to satisfy any barbecue aficionados. Rib tips, ribs, brisket, everything is delicious and fresh. The maple bacon sides are unlike any other that I’ve tried. The brisket sandwich is VERY filling. The prices have increased a bit since before the fire, but the quality hasn’t diminished a bit. Great barbecue right there on Taylor Street!
Overpriced, small portions, sandwiches are more toppings than meat. Have to order sides separately from the sandwiches. Only two sauces and they are subpar. Save your money and go elsewhere
Best bbq in the city! Ambiance is a little lack luster, but the food can’t be beat.

Conclusion: Disappointed  My fiance and I were on our second date, sitting at the bar, when the fire broke out and we were evacuated mid-meal by the bartender. We hung around for a while watching the firefighters work. It was dramatic.  Since then, I had been dying for the place to reopen so we could go back and relive the wonderful experience and reorder the food we didn't get to finish.  Today, we finally went back and it was underwhelming.  1. It is now counter style ordering. No table service. i.e. no friendly waitress/waiter telling you the specials or recommendations.  2. The prices are too high for no good reason. i.e. $12 for Texas Brisket (small portion and plain; no sides, no nothing) and $5 for a mediocre-sized portion of sweet potato fries.  3. Apparently, they no longer participate with the Wisely app.  4. The food does not taste the same. Definitely not as delicious as it used to be.  I could have lived with the new layout if they delivered on everything else. However, given the pricing and flavor changes, I will not go out of my way (I live in Oak Lawn) to visit County. I will stick to local barbecue joints where I can get better food for much less.

No one answering phone line listed on FB & the website. I wanted to bring my grandson to this newly reopened restaurant, but there were reports that it ran out in the first opening days. Nice to have loyal returning customers, but I don't want to come from Southern IL only to find you have run out !  Please answer your phones.
Great service, great environment, perfect food. We took the bus all the way from downtown. Loved it.

I definitely don't agree with C. Clark, I had some of my friends brisket today. It was melt in your mouth soft and shredded easy. I had the smoked chicken sandwich, Mac and cheese, and pork puppies. The chicken was good! Was it the best smoked chicken ever? No. It was juicy, and well seasoned which is the main concern. The BBQ sauce elevated it well. The sauce is a unique blend that is extremely different for the region that I haven't had before. Spicy blows house away in my mind. When they spicy, they mean hot. It's equal to a jalapenos bite, but it a great compliment to the flavors.  The Mac and cheese at a glance honestly looks subpar, but the cheeses they used to make the sauce compliment it well. The noodles were cooked perfectly, a solid piece in addition to the menu.  The pork puppies were my favorite part of the meal. They were by far the best hush puppy I have ever had in all of my lifetime. I would come back here simply for those alone. The sauce that is served with it is somehow a bit sour and tangy and was absolutely phenomenal. My only complaint towards this establishment was the prices of the side dishes. For 5 dollars each, or 3 for 12, it still feels like you barely get anything for the price paid. While they are high quality ingredients it still was a bit pricey.  It could be simply just because of the location, but is still is how I feel. Overall, so far the best BBQ spot I've found and I can't wait to continue to try new things on the menu.
What is going on with this place?  They suggested they would be closed for a short period of time (after a small fire) and now have been closed forever, it would appear.
Even despite the fire (not their fault) this place still deserves a bib gourmand award.  Great kitchen.  Great people.  Great BBQ.
Cool vibe, awesome staff, food was pretty good!
They doubled the price on rib tip Tuesdays so I shook the dust off my feet.
A surprisingly good barbeque place.  Their brisket is top-quality.  Do not skimp here or you will regret it.

They have some of the best barbecue for their age in Little Italy, a they smoke everything themselves. However, while still delicious, it does get repetitive, and I wish they would add some more menu items, but that may just be me.
Very good Bbq !!
The best ribs with the best texan beer!
(Translated by Google) Give me a warning in Chicago 100 by 100 for a week  (Original) اطيني انذار بشيكاغو 100 ب100 لمدة اسبوع
Decor was good, drinks were good, the food was delicious and i dont even eat nobody's coleslaw. Really good job guys. Sam did a great job all by himself.
Great meats. Better sides. Patio is nice
Love the atmosphere. And the food is even better! The brisket melts in your mouth. Also try the smoked bacon. Will absolutely be back!

A quality BBQ joint with friendly service and a cozy atmosphere.  This is a restaurant for serious BBQ snobs.  The portions are very large, so you'll want to come very hungry.  Also, be prepared to pay a somewhat high bill for this high-end BBQ neighborhood joint.  Staff was super friendly.

First of all,  the staff is very friendly and welcoming, so that goes a long way.  By advertisement and reviews there was no indication that this is more bar and very little restaurant. Had we known this before walking in for a late lunch on a Tuesday afternoon,  we would not have taken our one-year old child. Since it is more bar than anything,  the menu was limited,  except for the mile long drinks list.  We ordered garlic fries, brisket sandwiches and mac and cheese for the baby. The baby wasn't impressed with the mac and cheese but like us, she thought the garlic fries were awesome!  The brisket sandwich was a bit zesty, but good. They carry many local craft brews which is always great if you are into that. The music was a good fit for the atmosphere, somewhere along the lines of garage rock maybe punk rock? Either way, it was good and the baby really got into it. Overall,  it is a nice place to visit without your children, unless early exposure to bar life is on par with your parenting style.  If you are in your 20's or like to pretend to be,  and if you like craft beer and garlic fries, give it a try.
It's a bar pretending to be a restaurant. BBQ is pretty good...albeit a bit zesty.
Friendly and attentive staff. Nice and comfy atmosphere.....and most importantly great food!😘
Great food, great drinks, and great service. What else can you ask for. Definitely needs more recognition in the Chicago BBQ scene.

Let me start by saying that this review is based on food that was delivered via Door Dash. The food tastes GREAT, but there are some issues with delivery. First off, the sides are smaller than if you would order in restaurant.   They forgot the bbq sauce. They forgot an order of chicken. The fries were cold to the touch.  Prices are kind of expensive, but the taste makes it worth it as long as the order is correct.
Great service, great food! Everything was delicious and the food came out in a timely manner. The rib tips, Mac and cheese, chili fries and pork stuffed hush puppies are out of this world good!
Awesome spot!  Some of the best BBQ in Chicago.  Highly recommend the 50 cent Rib Tip Tuesday special.  Massive tips!
Great vibes. Awesome pulled pork sandwich. Modern/rustic outdoor patio with good music. A must for summer  Chicago BBQ.

Didn't have a chance to eat here.  Saw it on Check Please! and wanted to try it.  Drove in from far western suburbs.  Called ahead to check on the wait time.  They stated they didn't take reservations.  No problem.  Get there and there are three tables open, but they won't seat us because the tables were for reservations!!!  If you don't take reservations, then DONT TAKE RESERVATIONS!  Went down the street and had a nice dinner at Francescas.  Not what we had planned, but worked out ok.  Wouldn't try it agan, there's plenty of other BBQ places.
Friendly staff and cozy environment mixed with fantastic barbeque food and sides.  Brisket and Mac n cheese was my favorite combo.

If the website and google say open, then you make your way here they better be open. Which they were not. If you can't control your internet presence why would I ever trust your biz again. Probably won't return
Great staff, excellently prepared barbecue. Really feels authentic and the side of fries is reason alone to go in!

Excellent fish tacos, cheddar grits and impeccable and friendly service. The smoked buffalo wings are very average although I have never been a fan of "smoked" buffalo wings but these were just too soggy in addition to too smokey

All of the staff is very friendly and they know their menu. I like the 'taste of county bbq' because you get a little bit of everything. Make sure you try one of their appetizers (hush puppies, garlic fries, CHILI PARFAIT). Be prepared for a long wait time if you arrive during peak hours.

I lived in the south for 8 years and this reminds me of the bbq in the south. I can honestly say everything on the menu is great and even the music in the restaurant is good. Kinda small looks bigger from the outside.

The menu of the location on Tayler street doesn't match the online menu. This location serves only one kind of burger that changes on a weekly basis. The burger that I've ordered was good but too pricey and small. I had betters. If you want a great burger, go somewhere else. Overall, good service, tiny place.
Great experience, quick and friendly service. Delicious food!

I came here the night they were featured on Check Please! and they were still able to keep check times down despite the flood of to-go and delivery orders!  I had two appetizers as my meal - the mac 'n cheese and garlic fries.  I loved the individual baked serving of mac 'n cheese - the crispy top was perfect.  The interior was decorated nicely and the bar tenders were very passionate about their jobs and added a little flare to their beverage making.  I will absolutely order out from here now that I know I'm in their boundary!
Fantastic meats, attentive service, and great Bourbon collection.

Amazing BBQ!! Ask for Izzy!!! First time here, mind blown! Came for dinner and the FOOD & SERVICE were amazing!!! We absolutely had to go back for lunch the next day. It was even better the 2nd time!! Must try the Smoked Pork Puppies, Brisket and Collard Greens. I am hoping they bring back the deviled eggs for my next visit :)

Came here on our first night in Chicago in search of BBQ food. Alot of my searches use Google and their rating system wether it seems a decent place to go. County didn't disappoint. Our server Jill was really nice food was good drink was good all at a decent price. Didn't leave hungry. As a guy from the UK, it's worth the travel too. It's also a bit out of town so the bars are generally quieter around here but still with a good atmosphere.

Friendly atmosphere and really good food.  Enjoyed it.  Collar greens, macaroni amd cheese, garlic fries.  Chicken sandwich cheddar grits and corn pudding were amongst the items tried. Very good and will return again!  And def try the corn pudding! :-)

Man, I love this place. The atmosphere, food, and drink all tie together for an authentic BBQ feel. They have great specials (mondays and tuesdays especially). However, my last visit had one particular hang up... flies. I was sitting at the bar and there were an incredible amount of fruit flies. It made me want to just get my food to go, but I stayed because I already had a cold pint. Otherwise this would be 5 stars. Maybe the flies were too extreme in preserving the authentic BBQ vibe...

All I can say is that I live in Texas, I love brisket, and thought I could find great brisket anywhere in Texas.  Well, that is not the case.  The Brisket I had here was mouth wattering and delicious.  The staff were all great.  I would recommend this to anyone in the mood for great food.

Stopped by here for dinner on a whim and very thankful we did.  The facility is small, there is a bar and a few tables so you may have a little wait on a busy night.  With a family of five, we had a little wait :)  There were some other patrons at the bar that kept our younger two entertained, and vice versa, and the bartender gave all three children some free lemonade while we waited (and it was good lemonade too!) and some garlic french fries.  The food was excellent all around, service was great and could not ask for a better atmosphere.  It was a little loud but certainly family friendly.  Loved it and would darn sure recommend.  Wish we lived just a little closer, though my waistline and wallet may not agree.

We ordered everything.  The good, the hot link. Way pricey but tasty.  The bad, the rest of the order. The Texas brisket had a 1/4 layer of fat holding all the great spice and no smoke penetrated it. Take the fat away it was mostly tasteless meat.  The Pulled Pork sandwich was filled with fatty pork.  The bread of the sandwich was blah.  Gina's Potatoes were not tasty save for the jalapeno peppers in it.  The chili smelled nice but again fatty meat in it.  The mac and cheese with burnt ends was okay but for $6 no thanks.  Oh yes the charity chicken nuggets were very good at least.  We were very bummed.  Maybe a bad day or a bad chef on our to go visit but we do not think we will go back with all the other choices we have, though this is closest to work.

What an incredible experience! I love this place! As a native of Kansas City, I've held my nose to local barbecue for decades. Our meal here was a wonderful and refreshing experience. The Kansas City burnt end is MAGNIFICENT! Full of flavor and taste! I hardly used any sauce! The mac and cheese was creamy and tangy, a great compliment to our meal. The hush puppies are filled with meat, cheese, and wonderfulness! We tasted the bread pudding; as with everything else, it was just very, very well-prepared.  We were lucky to find street parking a couple of blocks away and walked over. There is paid parking on the street and valet parking, very nearby. This restaurant is in a vibrant and rising culinary community.
Excellent food and exceptional service.  The rib tips are so tender and the sides that we tried were amazing.  I will definitely be back.

amazing! so reminds me of texas...they really care for their meats and the mac n cheese with burnt ends! where has this dish been all my life.... they deliver but i say come in for the staff and the lovely collection of bourbons.... everthing falls apart....soooo yummy! get here

Being from the south I've always found it tough to find good BBQ in the city. County more than fills the void. The chicken and ribs were great. Great atmosphere and very knowledgeable staff makes this a great place to get BBQ and a beer.
Excellent food and atmosphere. If you're a Bourbon drinker you have to try one of their specialties
One word: Exceptional. Get the blackened cauliflower side and try to sit at Pablo's tables. He's the bartender.

Best smoked barbecue in town.  The restaurant is small and seats about 40 people.  The service is fast and the staff is friendly. The smoked bacon bar bites, BLT sliders and brisket chili are mouth-watering. Texas Brisket is delicious and melts in your mouth.  The Chicago rib tips and garlic fries are good too.  I didn’t care for the fried green tomatoes.  They were a little salty.  I would recommend “A Taste of County BBQ” platter to sample a few different menu items.   Highly recommended!

Small, home-y feel with a great BBQ selection--wish the Pulled Pork was a permanent dish rather than a special, but it was still fantastic. Note that they don't have ketchup. And if you like County Barbeque be sure to try DMK Burger Bar!

I stopped here after discovering Honkey Tonk BBQ didn't open until 4pm. Had a taste for beef brisket and KNEW I wasn't going to get outside and make my own. After reading the previous reviews I opted for the brisket sandwich and fried green tomatoes. Service was VERY friendly and the restaurant is very nice and quaint. Bar looked to have a nice selection of beers as well.  Seeing as such I hate to say anything negative about the place however I feel the previous reviews are a bit misleading. The brisket sandwich is SMALL, I'm used to going to a bbq place and if I'm paying $9 bucks for a sandwich, I expect it to be good for one and big for $9.... The brisket itself is decently smoky but it is very dry, and the portion I don't even think is /was a 1/4lb. All the sauces are meh as I tried all three. The mustard is deccent if you like mustard sauce, the spicy to me tastes best of all three, the house sauce just tastes strange as it has ALOT of terragon in it. Maybe thats what is throwing me off as I am not used to terragon in BBQ anywhere Ive had BBQ, and Ive been to alot of joints. The ciabatta roll is a nice touch, but if you think about the size of a standard roll you can picture the amount of meat I'm talking about when I say it definitely did not overtake the little ciabatta roll.  The garlic fries we're definitely the pinnacle of my experience, flavorful, perfectly salted and fried to a crunchy awesomeness. The fried green tomatoes on the other hand....  I have absolutely no idea what the other person was talking about, although decent they are nothing to write home about. First of all, so you know...  You only get THREE slices of tomato (with a side of goat cheese for dipping ) for SIX dollars. I don't know about you, but to me, I feel hoodwinked, led astray and run amuck for paying $2 per slice of tomato. Although the service and atmosphere are nice, food is key so I simply cannot recommend this place seeing all of the other great BBQ joints in the city. Maybe a good addition to the area but just not for me.
This place has some of the best bbq I've ever tasted! Service is excellent too!! The brisket and fried green tomatoes are to die for!!!

When I heard this was from the same people who started DMK Burger Bar, I had to go!  The Little Italy neighborhood is a hike for me since I live on the north side, but it was totally worth it.  I went during it's grand opening week and the wait wasn't bad, which is surprising because it's quite small inside.  The food is a great addition to the Chicago barbeque scene.  My ribs were cooked perfectly and I mean PERFECTLY!  They were tender and just fell right off the bone.  We also started with the wedge salad.  It's not your typical wedge salad, so don't be surprised, but it was also really good.  The only thing I think they could work on is their housemade barbeque sauces, they were not my favorite.  I definitely recommend venturing to Little Italy and checking this restaurant out.

Great food, quick service, brisket is mind-blowig, and incredible corn pudding!  Could use more beer selections but overall, a great addition to the area.  Great place.  Awesome place.  Must. Go. There.
